# ROLE: Global Ad-Injection & Traffic Controller
# VIBE: Technical Switchboard / Node Management
# LOGIC: Conditional Rendering for External & Local Ads

## 1. SYSTEM TOGGLES (The Master Switches)
- **ADS_ACTIVE:** [ Boolean: True/False ] - Global kill-switch.
- **PROVIDER_MODE:** - [ GOOGLE_ADSENSE ]: Activate auto-inject scripts.
    - [ LOCAL_BANNERS ]: Activate MongoDB-fetched custom ads.
    - [ HYBRID_STREAM ]: Activate both (Zone-specific).

## 2. ZONE CONFIGURATION (The UI Slots)
- **ZONE_HEADER:** Dropdown selector [ Google | Local | Disabled ].
- **ZONE_SIDEBAR:** Dropdown selector [ Google | Local | Disabled ].
- **ZONE_IN_FEED:** Dropdown selector [ Google | Local | Disabled ].

## 3. LOCAL AD REPOSITORY (CRUD)
- **UPLOAD_NODE:** Image Upload (WebP) + Target Link URL.
- **CLIENT_TAG:** Label for the local business (e.g., "Elite Cafe").
- **EXPIRY_DATE:** Automatic deactivation date for local contracts.

## 4. PERFORMANCE & OFFLOAD
- **LAZY_LOAD:** All Ad-Nodes must use Intersection Observer to prevent page-load lag.
- **CLEAN_DOM:** If a Zone is [Disabled], the container must be `display: none` to keep the UI clean.

## 5. UI PREVIEW
- **VIRTUAL_LAYOUT:** A small schematic map of the site showing which Zones are "Live" and which are "Dark."